Rustenburg A woman and a man were arrested in Hebron outside Brits on Thursday for possession of dagga with an estimated street value of R1.6 million, North West police said. Colonel Emelda Setlhako said a joint operation conducted by the police in Hebron and the Tshwane metro police led to the arrest of a woman 34, and a man, 31. &quot;The suspects were busted today [on Thursday] at Midas Section, Hebron after the police got a tip-off that the suspects were dealing in dagga. Upon searching the house, the police found plastics bags containing dagga with an estimated street value of R1.6 million.&quot; The two were expected to appear in the Ga-Rankuwa Magistrate's Court soon on a charge of possession of dagga. African News Agency